@ekbiker I'm sorry to say, but I don't think that's really how it's going to work out. I am making a Hugging Face robot in my house right now, but it's mostly an assembly thing. A humanoid robot requires a lot more than that. 

While you could certainly buy all the pieces from China, you would then be just like every other robot company. I don't see it that way, and I don't believe you'll be able to build your own world model that can compete with, for instance, a Grok-run world model in an Optimus Tesla robot. 

Maybe there is a play there, but I don't know. It's tough to see it happening because of the sheer amount of training required to develop the model, train the robot, and get everything to work. I simply don't see this as a garage project.

